<TABLE BORDER=0 cellpadding=4 border=0 cellspacing=1 WIDTH="95%"><TR bgcolor="#000000"><TD COLSPAN=2><CENTER><FONT SIZE="2" COLOR="#00ff00" FACE="Verdana, Arial">T O P I C  &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; R E V I E W</font></CENTER></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Shaggy</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">A friend of mine got banned while in game, as the GM told him, "for using Winhack." Period. This person did indeed have Winhack running on his machine as I use its API for the GUI version of an EQHack program. This tells us one of 2 things... <p>1) Someone who knew he was "using Winhack" (and only 4 of his close online friends knew) ratted him out, <p>OR<p>2) Verant has a list of "proscribed" programs that it checks for. While its true no directory listing is sent back to the server, it could be a simple true/false flag if one of the proscribed programs was detected.  <p>I am nearly 100% certain it is #2, above. Regardless, if you are using any widely used "hack" type program, including any of the programs available here, you should definatley rename any executables to be safe -- and I can gaurantee you Verant doesn't give a rat's ass if it is legal for them to check for other running executables on your machine or not. <p>Hopefully Ashran, Loony and the others will give this some consideration and start allowing for changed names on such things as .dlls -- as in you choose a custom name when you install the program.<p>Food for thought, <p>~~ Shaggy
</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I am toying with this idea, thanks for the input :)
</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Bushman</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">One thing no one thinks of is the fact that at patch the patching software grinds through all of the files in your EQ directories and then compares them to a list on the server to determine if you need the patch, You give permission for this in the agreement you say "accept" on everytime you log on.<p>It only follows that they would have also listed "Bad" files in this check and all they have to do is flag an account for whatever they want when it shows up... its a simple file list and compare.<p>Actually busting the person is easy .. all they do is flag the account that has the "illegal" proggy in it and then check that accounts logs for discrepancies... they dont even have to say you have it all they have to do is say "We saw wierd activity in a log and so we looked deeper... So sorry your gone." end of story.  <p>The moral... as any "Un-caught" hacker or cracker will tell you ....<p>"Don't use your primary account or any machine that can be traced to you for purposes of experimentation, or some time no matter how careful you are you will get nailed for it."  <p>Why do you think there are so few Hackers that are well known.??. Its because the "REALLY" good ones don't ever make a mistake that can be traced to them. Hence they are not known by anyone except maybe a close friend.<p>Be smarter than the software, after all it only does what we tell it to.
</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Ashran</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Maybe thats one of the reasons why the program does only load the client and not the patcher ;)
</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">The Darkening</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Do you want to know whats horrible? I've run WinHack on MANY occasions, EQ Inside, EQViewer, EQZone, etc.. all these apps are still in my EverQuest folder. I run WinHack most everytime I boot up, just to watch the memory information, but I never change anything. Also with some information I have, GMs can not tell you're using WinHack unless someone else mentions you are *veg*.
</FONT></TD></TR><TR bgcolor="#1f1f1f"><TD valign=top><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Acid</FONT></TD><TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">they can tell if you are running it, but they cant use that as an excuse because its illegal.  however you have to watch out for any hack programs that alter any of the files that come with eq, or any of the data being sent back and forth.
</FONT></TD></TR></TABLE>
</FONT>
